materialized_view_ids.description: Map of fully qualified materialized view ids keyed by view ids.

table_ids.description: Map of fully qualified table ids keyed by table ids.

view_ids.description: Map of fully qualified view ids keyed by view ids.

access.description: Map of access rules with role and identity type. Keys are arbitrary and must match those in the `access_identities` variable, types are `domain`, `group`, `special_group`, `user`, `view`.

access_identities.description: Map of access identities used for basic access roles. View identities have the format 'project_id|dataset_id|table_id'.

authorized_datasets.description: An array of datasets to be authorized on the dataset.

authorized_routines.description: An array of authorized routine to be authorized on the dataset.

authorized_views.description: An array of views to be authorized on the dataset.

dataset_access.description: Set access in the dataset resource instead of using separate resources.

encryption_key.description: Self link of the KMS key that will be used to protect destination table.

iam.description: IAM bindings in {ROLE => [MEMBERS]} format. Mutually exclusive with the access_* variables used for basic roles.

project_id.description: Id of the project where datasets will be created.

tables.description: Table definitions. Options and partitioning default to null. Partitioning can only use `range` or `time`, set the unused one to null.

custom_roles.description: Ids of the created custom roles.

service_accounts.description: Product robot service accounts in project.

services.description: Service APIs to enabled in the project.

sink_writer_identities.description: Writer identities created for each sink.

auto_create_network.description: Whether to create the default network for the project.

compute_metadata.description: Optional compute metadata key/values. Only usable if compute API has been enabled.

contacts.description: List of essential contacts for this resource. Must be in the form EMAIL -> [NOTIFICATION_TYPES]. Valid notification types are ALL, SUSPENSION, SECURITY, TECHNICAL, BILLING, LEGAL, PRODUCT_UPDATES.

custom_roles.description: Map of role name => list of permissions to create in this project.

default_service_account.description: Project default service account setting: can be one of `delete`, `deprivilege`, `disable`, or `keep`.

descriptive_name.description: Name of the project name. Used for project name instead of `name` variable.

group_iam.description: Authoritative IAM binding for organization groups, in {GROUP_EMAIL => [ROLES]} format. Group emails need to be static. Can be used in combination with the `iam` variable.

iam_bindings.description: Authoritative IAM bindings in {KEY => {role = ROLE, members = [], condition = {}}}. Keys are arbitrary.

iam_bindings_additive.description: Individual additive IAM bindings. Keys are arbitrary.

lien_reason.description: If non-empty, creates a project lien with this description.

logging_data_access.description: Control activation of data access logs. Format is service => { log type => [exempted members]}. The special 'allServices' key denotes configuration for all services.

logging_exclusions.description: Logging exclusions for this project in the form {NAME -> FILTER}.

logging_sinks.description: Logging sinks to create for this project.

metric_scopes.description: List of projects that will act as metric scopes for this project.

org_policies.description: Organization policies applied to this project keyed by policy name.

org_policies_data_path.description: Path containing org policies in YAML format.

parent.description: Parent folder or organization in 'folders/folder_id' or 'organizations/org_id' format.

prefix.description: Optional prefix used to generate project id and name.

project_create.description: Create project. When set to false, uses a data source to reference existing project.

service_encryption_key_ids.description: Cloud KMS encryption key in {SERVICE => [KEY_URL]} format.

service_perimeter_bridges.description: Name of VPC-SC Bridge perimeters to add project into. See comment in the variables file for format.

service_perimeter_standard.description: Name of VPC-SC Standard perimeter to add project into. See comment in the variables file for format.

shared_vpc_host_config.description: Configures this project as a Shared VPC host project (mutually exclusive with shared_vpc_service_project).

shared_vpc_service_config.description: Configures this project as a Shared VPC service project (mutually exclusive with shared_vpc_host_config).

skip_delete.description: Allows the underlying resources to be destroyed without destroying the project itself.

tag_bindings.description: Tag bindings for this project, in key => tag value id format.
